####node
The node query uniquely identifies a *node* type in your API. This can return an object of any type implementing the *node* interface. You should use fragments to handle the various return types.

For example

    {
        node(id: "X") {
            ... on User {
                id
                name
            }
            ... on OtherNodeType {
                id
                title
            }
        }
    }
